node.text:
I love this photograph, it’s so captivating! It’s made even more so because I don’t know its history. I think it’s probably one of those photos from the Edwardian era, where people would dress up in a range of different costumes and pose as other people or characters just for fun.

It doesn’t really matter that the women were not likely to be real witches, it’s still a cool photo and a piece of history.

What do you think?

Lindsay 💜

✨ P𝕣𝕒𝕔𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕒𝕝 W𝕚𝕥𝕔𝕙𝕔𝕣𝕒𝕗𝕥 T𝕚𝕡𝕤✨
Egg shells have so many magickal uses, but before they are used, make sure they have been cleansed and the inner membrane removed so the shells are hygienic.

There are two ways to dry the shells, you can let them simply air dry, or if you need them faster, place them on a baking tray covered and bake at the lowest temperature your oven will go on for 10 minutes.

Does anyone know a good vegan alternative to egg shells? Someone once told me that sea shells and even nuts can be used 🤷🏼‍♀️

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
🪴 E𝕒𝕣𝕥𝕙 🪴 
Elemental magick forms a large part of my Craft so I thought I post some info about the elements and their correspondence. These items, like herbs and crystals are all things aligned with the element of Earth so can be incorporated in to spells or rituals to help you connect more with the ground beneath our feet. 

Left to right in the graphic represents: direction, the qualities of  Earth, zodiac signs, colours, crystals, herbs, physical items that can be used to symbolise Earth, planets.

Working with the elements is a great form of magick for those at the start of their Witchcraft journey. The beauty of this magick is in its simplicity. The elements can be represented by simple ingredients such as a glass of water (Water), soil/crystals (Earth), incense (Air) and a candle (Fire).

What element do you connect with the most?

Lindsay 💜

node.text:
✨𝕆𝕣𝕒𝕔𝕝𝕖 ℝ𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨
1. 𝕊𝕠𝕦𝕥𝕙 ℕ𝕠𝕕𝕖 ☋
The South Node reveals the challenges and gifts we bring in from previous lifetimes. It represents our fears and our insecurities. Have you been struggling to control your fears lately? You may even feel like your fears are controlling you. The South Node suggests these fears may be an overdeveloped character trait from your other lives that you find easy to fall back on (it’s familiar) but that may undermine your growth. The key to overcoming these fears is to embrace them - take on the things that bring you fear. You are more than strong enough, and once you start, you may realise you were worrying far too much. Don’t let your fears paralyse you

2. ℙ𝕒𝕝𝕝𝕒𝕤 𝔸𝕥𝕙𝕖𝕟𝕖 
Pallas Athene, an asteroid, can come as a flash of insight or sudden creative inspiration. Things may have been stressful recently, but you need to shift your perspective in order to understand what you need to do to move forward. This card represents your ability to connect with your intuition and higher self. Have you been ignoring your intuition lately? Connecting with your intuition will help you shift your perspective and you need to be open to what it’s telling you. You might feel you’ve lost touch and perspective with your goals, but this card is encouragement to get things back on track

3. 𝕃𝕒𝕤𝕥 ℚ𝕦𝕒𝕣𝕥𝕖𝕣 
This card represents the letting go of blockages so you are able to actively move toward in a positive direction. You may be feeling somehow stuck, but The Last Quarter brings in the transitional energy that makes moving forward possible. But to make this change, you must actively practice self forgiveness. Are you too hard on yourself? It’s time to be more loving and patient towards yourself as you are with others. Forgive yourself for the things that didn’t work out and free yourself from the limiting energy that comes along with not cutting yourself some slack. Making this adaption is crucial to help prepare you for the new things coming your way. It will help you navigate with ease any challenges and obstacles. 

#tarot #divination #healing #witch #witchcraft #witchy #witches #energy #witchythings #witchystuff
